    "form_header_text": "FY27 Appropriations (Programmatic and Language) Request Form - Rep. Shri Thanedar",
    "form_instructions_text": "Thank you for your interest in pursuing Programmatic and Language Request Funding. Each year through the appropriations process, Congress allocates money for offices, programs, and grants administered by the federal government. As a Member of Congress, Congressman Thanedar advocates for priorities and programs that benefit Michigan's 13th District through the appropriations process. A Programmatic Request is a request to fund a general federal agency or program at a specified level. A Language Request is a request to add language to the yearly appropriations bill, such as bill or report language that does not direct funding to a particular entity but encourages, urges, or directs some type of action by an agency. Please note: This is NOT the Community Project Funding Application. Multiple requests in one submission will NOT be accepted.",
